<title>USA: Potash Corp files $1 bln debt shelf.</title>
<headline>Potash Corp files $1 bln debt shelf.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Potash Corp of Saskatchewan Inc filed Friday with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission a shelf registration to sell up to $1 billion in debt securities.</p>
<p>Net proceeds will be used for general corporate purposes including working capital, capital expenditures and repayment of debt, Potash said in the filing.</p>
<p>The Canadian company, based in Saskatoon, is in the integrated fertilizer business.</p>
